to setup the spring boot project, go to spring initializer in google.
from there set the latest version of springboot and the version of java of which u have JDK
then download the zip file and extract it.
open the folder in intellij / any other IDE u r using and its good to go.

to install a dependency follow the steps:
1. go to online maven repo for spring boot dependency
2. copy paste the XML code for that dependency in the pom.xml (POM = project object model)
3. rerun the maven project using right click and then sync project in maven options.
4. the dependency will be installed

structure of the contents in the springboot directory:
1. main - contains the functions/codes etc.
2. test - contains the unit test functionality that is required to test the application

inside main there 2 dir-
1. java - this contains all the code
2. resources - this contains static data like images, videos etc to be displayed

inside the java folder we have the com. package and inside that we create all the further dir
we want to